"{\"uid\": \"newseu.cgtn.com-news-2024-07-18-Paris-on-two-wheels-Why-the-Olympic-host-is-now-a-cycling-city-1vjUoT4varC-p.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can change your cookie settings through your browser.\", \"from\": 146, \"to\": 203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ross Cullen in Paris  Copied  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u008cThe eyes of the world will soon be on Paris for the Olympics.\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 299, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 205, \"end\": 209, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ross_Geller\", \"score\": 0.9999986542729817, \"rank\": 1.3403603906526006e-06, \"text\": \"Ross\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ross_Geller\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ross_Geller\"}, {\"begin\": 210, \"end\": 216, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Cullen\", \"score\": 0.9630505051892077, \"rank\": 0.0383623058203542, \"text\": \"Cullen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Cullen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matt_Cullen\"}, {\"begin\": 220, \"end\": 225, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999947704, \"rank\": 5.127196097084742e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 276, \"end\": 281, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999947704, \"rank\": 5.127196097084742e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French capital will be a city on two wheels \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 and on a quest to cut emissions.\", \"from\": 300, \"to\": 384, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 304, \"end\": 310, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999177869260597, \"rank\": 7.302713475233763e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Cycling is now Parisians' second-favorite way to commute, behind walking.\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 459, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A new report shows more people travel by bike than car because it's quicker, and visitors to the French capital for the Olympics are being advised to consider two wheels where possible.\", \"from\": 460, \"to\": 645, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 557, \"end\": 563, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9999177869260597, \"rank\": 7.302713475233763e-05, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"More than 60 kilometers of bike paths will link the Games venues and 10,000 bike-rack spaces will be added to existing ones.\", \"from\": 647, \"to\": 771, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Metro and buses are also an option, but some metro stations near Olympic venues will be closed - meaning that hopping on a bike should be one of the smoothest ways to get around during the Games.\", \"from\": 773, \"to\": 968, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the cycle lanes have not escaped the impact of Paris 2024.\", \"from\": 970, \"to\": 1032, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1021, \"end\": 1031, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.3852680965582354e-14, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Traffic jams, diversions and the closure of cycle lanes are problems that have been part of the daily life of Parisian riders for weeks.\", \"from\": 1033, \"to\": 1169, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"READ MORE  Solar cars and tyre dust: Auto's future at Goodwood Festival of Speed  Mackerel getting Norwegian fishermen out of deep water  The UK village that inspired the Olympic Games  A cyclist rides a self-service Velib bike by the Alexandre III bridge Olympic site with the Grand-Palais in the background.\", \"from\": 1171, \"to\": 1480, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1270, \"end\": 1279, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"score\": 0.9956113016496321, \"rank\": 0.00266839237474438, \"text\": \"Norwegian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norway\"}, {\"begin\": 1313, \"end\": 1315, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9997698218127259, \"rank\": 0.00022990851143809185, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/Ludovic Marin/AFP  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u008cParis does have plenty of bike lanes and it is starting to be more bike-friendly but it's no Amsterdam or Copenhagen - yet.\", \"from\": 1481, \"to\": 1627, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1597, \"end\": 1606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\", \"score\": 0.9739962037598422, \"rank\": 0.026558585912722733, \"text\": \"Amsterdam\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\"}, {\"begin\": 1610, \"end\": 1620, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copenhagen\", \"score\": 0.9800869882393979, \"rank\": 0.020250780476766102, \"text\": \"Copenhagen\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copenhagen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Copenhagen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Plus many cyclists do not respect road rules - such as stopping at red lights.\", \"from\": 1628, \"to\": 1706, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u008cFrom just 200 kilometers in 2001, cyclists now have more than 1,000 kilometers of tailor-made bike paths.\", \"from\": 1708, \"to\": 1816, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Often concreted off from the rest of the road, these separated lanes provide greater safety for cyclists.\", \"from\": 1817, \"to\": 1922, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u008cVelib is a bike-for-hire scheme that started in Paris in 2007, and 3,000 additional rapid-hire Velib bikes will be put into service for the duration of the Games.\", \"from\": 1924, \"to\": 2089, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1975, \"end\": 1980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999947704, \"rank\": 5.127196097084742e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There are also private companies like Lime and Dott providing thousands of bikes to meet growing demand.\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2194, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u008cAnd if cycling in Paris needed another boost - the men's and women's Olympic road cyclists will soon be racing around the city.\", \"from\": 2196, \"to\": 2326, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2217, \"end\": 2222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999947704, \"rank\": 5.127196097084742e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Subscribe toStoryboard: A weekly newsletterbringing you the best of CGTN every Friday  SIT